
-> '@Model*(org.apache.sling.model.annotations)' annotation is used to convert the basic java class into the sling model 
	 ex: @Model(adaptables = Resource.class, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)


->  adaptables - resource types to which the model can be adapted. A Model can be adapted to both Resource and SlingHttpServletRequest.


-> adapters – adapters to which the model can be adapted
	ex: @Model(adaptables = Resource.class, adapters=ContactUsModel, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
	
	
-> '@ValueMapValue' annotation injects the properties from the JCR dialog to the model.
	The ValueMap is an easy way to access the properties of a resource.


-> '@Inject' -> fields that are needed to be injected in the sling model.


-> '@Named' annotation is used to inject property like sling:resourceType.
-	If the field name differs from the property name, consider using the @Named annotation
	ex: 
@ValueMapValue @Named("jcr:title")
private String title;


-> '@PostConstruct' annotation is used on a method that runs after injecting all of the properties to perform any initialization and we then write the logic part in this annotation
- It is the same as JAVA main method.


-> '@Optional, @Required, @Default(values=....)' ; these annotations are used according to the requirement.

	ex: 
@Model(adaptables = SlingHttpServletRequest.class, adapters=ContactUsModel, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
public class ContactUsModelImpl implements ContactUsModel{
        @ValueMapValue
	private String mailAddress;
        @ValueMapValue
        @Required
	private String phoneNumber;


-> '@ChildResource' annotations is used to inject child resource by its name.
ex:
@Model(adaptables = Resource.class, adapters=ContactUsModel, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
public class ContactUsModelImpl implements ContactUsModel{
       @ChildResource (name="mailAddress")
       private Resource child_node_of_current_resource;  // Fetches a child resource named "mailAddress"
       @ChildResource
       private List<Resource> emailAddress;  // Fetches multiple child resources under "emailAddress" child Node 
        
		
-> '@ScriptVariable' annotation is used to inject any sightly global objects into the sling model.
  ex. component, currentNode, currentPage, pageManager, etc.....
 this annotation can only be used with adaptables as "SlingHTTPServletRequest", 
 otherwise it will show NullPointerException.
ex:
@Model(adaptables = SlingHttpServletRequest.class, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
public class ContactUsModelImpl implements ContactUsModel{
    @ScriptVariable
    private Component component;
    @ScriptVariable
    private ComponentContext componentContext;
    @ScriptVariable
    private Design currentDesign;
}
	

-> "@SlingObject" annotation is used to inject the sling objects in sling model.
The supported Sling objects include SlingHttpServletRequest, SlingHttpServletResponse, Resource, ResourceResolver, and SlingScriptHelper.
ex:
@Model(adaptables = Resource.class, adapters=ContactUsModel, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
public class ContactUsModelImpl implements ContactUsModel{
       @SlingObject
       private SlingHttpServletRequest slingHttpServletRequest;  // Injects the request
       @SlingObject
       private SlingHttpServletResponse slingHttpServletResponse;  // Injects the response
       @SlingObject
       private Resource currentResource;  // Injects the current resource
       @SlingObject
       private ResourceResolver resourceResolver;  // Injects the resource resolver
   }
   

-> "@Self" ; Injects the adaptable object itself . This annotation is used to get the adaptable object.
ex:
 @Self
    protected Resource resource;
	

-> '@Via' ; In some cases, a different object should be used as the adaptable instead of the original adaptable. 
This can be done using the @Via annotation.
ex:  @Inject @Via(value = "jcr:content", type = ChildResource.class)


-> "@RequestAttribute" annotation is used to inject any request attribute from the sightly.
 while using the sling model, if we want to pass some parameters from the sightly to the sling model, then we can use this annotation.
 ex:
 @Model(adaptables = SlingHttpServletRequest.class, adapters=ContactUsModel, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
public class ContactUsModelImpl implements ContactUsModel{
       @RequestAttribute(name = "area")
       private String areaParam;  // Injects a request attribute named "area"

 
=> @Component:
 it marks the Java class as an OSGi Component as well as registers it as an OSGi Service.
 Only @Component annotation is not sufficient to implement the OSGI service so
 it is recommended to implement an interface.


=> @Reference:
 It also allows the dependencies injection of other OSGi services using the '@Reference' annotation.


=>  @ProviderType:
 this annotation defines that the only implementation in this bundle will only implement this interface(is bundle me jo bhi implementation hogi vo bs us interface ko implement kregi) 


=> @ConsumerType:
 this annotation means that we are expecting that the other OSGI bundle have it's own OSGI implementation which will implement the OSGI service interface.


=> @Version("....."):
 this annotation defines the version of the package.


=> '@OSGiService' :
 this annotation is used to let Sling Models inject an OSGi service.
ex:
@Model(adaptables = SlingHttpServletRequest.class, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
public class ContactUsModelImpl implements ContactUsModel {
    // Inject an OSGi service of type SomeService
    @OSGiService
    private SomeService someService;
}

 
=> '@ObjectClassDefinition' :
 this annotation provide the UI for the configuration.

 
=> @Designate(ocd=_______):
To use the configuration interface within our OSGI service component, we need this annotation.
 ex. @Designate(ocd = Cars.configurationName.class)

 
=> @AttributeDefinition 
 this annotation accepts some parameters where we are implementing this annotation.

 
=> @SlingServletResourceTypes :
  this annotation takes care of writing the service properties which is used by SlingServletResolver to register the annoted servlet component as servlet for specific resource type.
  
  
=>  @ResourcePath
The annotation is used to inject one or multiple resources.
ex:
@Model(adaptables = Resource.class, adapters=ContactUsModel, defaultInjectionStrategy = DefaultInjectionStrategy.OPTIONAL)
public class ContactUsModelImpl implements ContactUsModel{
       @ResourcePath(path = "/content/sourcedcode/en/home")
       Resource techrevelHomeRes;
}




